        <section class="project project--1 pt-lg-12 pt-7 pb-3">
          <div class="container" data-aos="zoom-up">
              <div class="row">
                  <div class="col-lg-7">
                    <div class="project__heading">
                        <h2 class="display-2 projects__header mb-0 pb-2">VR Interaction Modes</h2>
                        <p class="h3 font-italic mt-lg-n1">Testing Three VR Apps</p>
                      </div>
          
                      <div class="project__wrap">
                          <h2 class="display-2 mb-1 projects__header">Summary</h2>
                          <p>
                              VR Experience Testing is a research project that seeks to test different modes of interaction in a 3D environment. The Gear VR was used with three apps and a diverse participant group. Virtual reality is still in it's infancy stages and understanding how users respond to different modes of interaction can assist future design and development in VR applications.  
                          </p>
                      </div>
          
                      <div class="project__wrap ">
                          <h2 class="display-2 mb-1 projects__header">Tasks & Responsibilities</h2>
                            <ul>
                                <li>Facilitating usability tests, statistical analysis.</li>
                                <li>Qualitative data collection</li>
                            </ul>
                      </div>

                    <div class="project__wrap ">
                        <h2 class="display-2 mb-1 projects__header">Design Tools / UX Methods</h2>
                        <p>System Usability Scale, Nielsen Heuristics, SPSS, Gazepoint Eye tracker</p>
                    </div>

                    <div class="project__wrap ">
                        <h2 class="display-2 mb-1 projects__header">Research Stages</h2>
                        <h3>Step 1: Literature Review</h3>
                        <p>VR Experience Testing is a research project that seeks to test different modes of interaction in a 3D environment. The Gear VR was used with three apps and a diverse participant group. Virtual reality is still in it's infancy stages and understanding how users respond to different modes of interaction can assist future design and development in VR applications.</p>
                    </div>

                    <div class="project__wrap">
                        <h3>Step 2: Finding the Games</h3>
                        <p>This project required a variety of vr interactions. I tried many games looking for the different interaction styles for testing. </p>
                    </div>

                    <div class="project__wrap">
                        <h3>Step 3: Recruiting Users</h3>
                        <p>I spent a couple days scouring the Oculus store for games. I did this because I am addicted to gaming AND so I could see the different interaction designs related to movement. </p>
                    </div>

                    <div class="project__wrap">
                        <h3>I found most apps fell into three categories:</h3>
                        <ul>
                            <li>1. User's fixation on an object or location prompts movement. App used: 'Lands End'.</li>
                            <li>2. User's control movement using the Gear VR controls. App used: 'Ocean Rift'.</li>
                            <li>3. User is stationary with control of camera view based on head movement.
                            App used: Wall Street Journal with a 360 degree video.</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>

                    <div class="project__wrap">
                        <h3>Step 4: Testing</h3>
                        <p>There were 12 participants (7 male, 5 female , Median age = 34, age range: 18-84).</p>
                    </div>

                    <div class="project__wrap">
                        <h3>The Procedure:</h3>
                        <ul>
                            <li>1. Consent form</li>
                            <li>2. User testing script</li>
                            <li>3. Randomly assigned app</li>
                            <li>4. Questionnaires (2)</li>
                            <li>5. Randomly assigned app</li>
                            <li>6. Questionnaires (2)</li>
                            <li>7. Final app</li>
                            <li>8. Questionnaires (3)</li>
                            <li>9. Debriefing</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                </div>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="container" data-aos="zoom-up">
                <div class="project__wrap text-center">
                    <h2 class="display-2 pb-5">Tools for User Testing</h2>
                    <div class="row">
                        <div class="col-lg-4 col-md-6 py-5 py-lg-0"><img class="img-fluid" src="/src/images/research1/GearVr.png" alt="GearVr"><span class="d-block text-center h3 mt-3">Gear VR</span></div>
